{"lemma":"سَرَبٌ","slug":"سَرَبٌ","root":"س.ر.ب","root_slug":"س-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَرَب","root":"سرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19460"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leak, to seep, to ooze","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leak, to let through","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَرِبَ (sariba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"burrow, den, lair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"offlet, offtake, air return, flue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flock (of birds etc.)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19460","headword_ar":"سَرَب","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subterranean excavation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA) of a wild animal, (S, * Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no passage through it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wakorN","text_ar":"وَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) such as has a passage through it is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1342},{"kind":"text","text":"termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaqN","text_ar":"نَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) of a wild animal, (K,) or of a fox, and likewise [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"den"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a lion, and of a hyena, and of a wolf; and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place into which a wild animal enters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraAbN","text_ar":"اَسْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A, Msb.) In the saying in the Kur [xviii. 60],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@t~axa*a","text_ar":"فَا@تَّخَذَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylahu fiY A@lobaHori sarabFA","text_ar":"سَبِيلَهُ فِى ا@لْبَحْرِ سَرَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the fish)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took its way into the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], Fr says that when the fish was restored to life by the water that came upon it from the fountain [of life], and fell into the sea, its way became congealed, and like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarab","text_ar":"سَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subterranean excavation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: Zj says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srbA","text_ar":"سربا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be considered as put in the accus. case in two ways; either as a second objective complement of the verb, or as an inf. n. [of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariba","text_ar":"سَرِبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: and AHát thinks that it here means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAbFA","text_ar":"ذَهَابًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a secret,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hidden, place of passage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as used by El-Moatarid Edh-Dhafaree, it means [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subterranean channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduit, by which water enters a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iT","text_ar":"حَايِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walled garden of palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN sarabN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road, in which people follow one another continuously."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flowing water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saribN","text_ar":"سَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water flowing from a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water dropping from the punctures made in the sewing"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a water-skin. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that is poured into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin for water or milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is new,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that the thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which it is sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may become moistened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to swell, and fill up the holes made in the sewing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","Mgh","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}